      <AlternateName>SC11</AlternateName>
      <ReleaseDate>2010-03-10T15:51:31Z</ReleaseDate>
      <Description>The SC11 experiment is a triaxial fluxgate magnetometer.  Each axis has a range of 0 to +/- 500 nT.  The sensor is mounted on a 4 m boom extended perpendicular to the spin axis.  The field vector is measured four times per second.  The output from the spin axis aligned sensor is also fed to a set of SC10 filter channels to provide the same frequency band outputs.  The bandwidth of this magnetometer output is ~100 Hz.  The same axis can be placed on a brodband channel. The filter output from SC10 provides a sensitivity of 10^-1 nT in the 20 to 200 Hz channel while the broadband output provides a sensitivity of 0.2 nT/V.</Description>
